Life will give you what you're WILLING to do and what you're WILLING to work for
 
One question that has really changed my life is
 
"Am I willing to do ____?"
 
Countless times I've thought about something over and over that I want, a certain life, a material item, a person etc
 
But then found myself sitting there wondering why I haven't gotten it?
 
Having an internal conversation if I am truly willing, changed that and allowed me to release things I previously wanted and the stress that came with continually not having it.
 
For example:
 
You say you want a new car.
 
This car will cost you "xxx" more per month. Which would require you to work extra hours on the weekend, or pick up a side gig to pay for.
 
Then ask yourself, "Am I willing to work more, have less free time, and create the extra money needed, for this new car?"
 
If the answer is no, it makes it much easier to release that desire as you have made the decision that you are willing to do what would be needed to acquire the car and thus value your time and freedom more. 
 
In turn you will more gratitude for the time you have, and the car you have.
 
Creating these conscious decisions through introspection will allow an immense amount of clarity into what you truly want and what you'll actually work for.

And sometimes you’ll realize, goals you have wont require as much work as the daunting idea you created.
 
I truly believe every person on this planet is capable of achieving and acquiring anything they want.
 
We've seen countless people with circumstances we cant even fathom, achieve prodigious success.
 
You are no different. You are capable of it, as long as you're willing.
